   Education Programs
   Providing strategic leadership in educational and laboratory-directed
   research activities


   The primary objective of the INEEL's Education and Research Initiative
   (ERI) program is to provide strategic leadership in educational and
   laboratory-directed research activities. INEEL educational programs
   work with students over the entire education continuum to ensure a
   future workforce that will continue the long-term mission of the INEEL.

   INEEL has a long history of supporting pre-college and college-level
   internships and fellowships. The Inland Northwest Research Alliance
   (INRA), consisting of seven universities, is a partner in the
   management team of Bechtel BWXT Idaho, LLC, the management and
   operating contractor for the INEEL. We expect that these partnerships
   will lead to joint INRA-INEEL research initiatives for university
   faculty and students.

   INEEL's education encompasses Pre-college (K-12) and university-level.
   You will find more information about these programs below and elsewhere
   on this Web site.

   Pre-college
   The K-12 Education Program reflects the science, engineering, and
   technology mission areas of the INEEL. It is an investment in the next
   generation workforce such that a talent pool for science and
   engineering is increased. Programs the INEEL supports are:
     * JASON Idaho
     * Teaming Teachers with INEEL (TTI)
     * Student Action Teams (SAT)
     * Math and Science Equipment Gift Program
     * Science Exposition
     * Scholastic Tournament
     * Adopt-a-School is supported as a part of DOE's Adopt-a-School
       program

   Contact:   Elda D Zounar-Harbour
              208-526-4491
              zouned@inel.gov

