   University Programs
   University Programs, in partnership with regional and national colleges
   and universities, and in collaboration with the Inland Northwest
   Research Alliance, supports the mission of the INEEL.

   Bechtel BWXT Idaho, LLC, the management and operating contractor for
   the INEEL, provides higher education opportunities for employees
   through the INEEL employee education programs, as well as offering
   various scholarship programs and the Bechtel Foundation Matching Gifts
   Program.

   Opportunities for non-employees include:
     * Practicum
     * Undergraduate Fellowship
     * Computer Science Power Fellowship Program
     * Graduate Fellowship
     * Postgraduate Internship
     * Faculty research and sabbatical fellowships

   By linking colleges, universities, DOE laboratory facilities, and INEEL
   scientists and engineers (mentors) in research and applied learning
   activities, University Programs helps meet the DOE and INEEL goals of
   fostering science and engineering literacy and developing a future
   qualified workforce.

   University Programs also coordinates with and directs the Mid-West
   Regional Resource Center for Innovations, which promotes regional
   technical outreach and provides commercialization assistance to
   inventors and innovators.

